# FlowOne SFTP session sync
#
# Drains new sshd / internal-sftp journal entries into the panel's
# sftp_sessions table (login / logout / duration / transfer bytes per
# additional restricted SFTP user). Runs as root because the ssh journal is
# root-readable. Idempotent + incremental (advances a stored journald cursor),
# so once-a-minute is safe and cheap.
#
# Install on server:
#   cp /var/www/vps-admin/agent/deploy/flowone-sftp-sessions.cron \
#      /etc/cron.d/flowone-sftp-sessions
#   chmod 0644 /etc/cron.d/flowone-sftp-sessions
#   systemctl restart cron   # or: service cron reload
#
# Requires:
#   - migrate_sftp_sessions.sql applied
#   - sshd Match block running `internal-sftp -l INFO` (SshdSftpConfigurator;
#     applied automatically the next time an SFTP user is created/repaired,
#     or run `sshd -t && systemctl reload ssh` after deploying the config)

* * * * * root /usr/local/lsws/lsphp83/bin/php /var/www/vps-admin/agent/scripts/sftp-session-sync.php >/dev/null 2>&1
